# Ban meta wording talk

When writing or editing Solmare chapters, **do not** reintroduce:

- *soft nouns*, *soft language*, *soft term*, *clean noun*, *wrong nouns*
- *invent words*, *invent a phrase*, *tomorrow's words*, *invent certainty* (as style)
- *finished label*, *better label*, *incomplete label*, *working label*, *fix the label*, *earned one*
- *strategic gift*, *as a gift*, *not a gift* (for maps / archive / disclosure — keep *gift* only for literal objects)
- *fringe* as default border noun (prefer *outer corridor* / *border* / *Neutral Zone edge*)
- *admit weather they cannot command* and similar elevated empire-aphorisms — say the real political problem
- *temporary politeness* — name the real ask
- *polite fiction* / *polite X* / *polite Y* as default irony (*polite misunderstanding*, *polite desks*) — say the real thing
- Distress/rescue hammering after the room has moved on — operational rules only
- *header cascade* / *Fleet's forms* as default mismatch language
- *argue* / *arguing* as default politics/process talk (*finished arguing*, *arguing about nouns*) — **Brenner only**, sparingly, usually hardware; see `Writing_System/Revision_Pass/03_clarity_language.md` §3.2a
- *lie / lying / lies / honest* as default metaphor for overcommitment, dual roles, bad readings, or institutional mismatch (*without lying to somebody*, *which panel lies*, *urn was honest*) — keep only for people actually deceiving; instruments fail to settle / look fine and are not; see Pass 3 §3.2c
- *the board* as vague catch-all — name the instrument (*shared traffic display*, *status display*, *packet queue*, *relay console*, *approach plot*); keep *board* for the verb or a literal named object; do **not** spam *traffic wall* / *status wall* every glance — name once, then *display* / *plot* / *queue*; see Pass 3 §3.2d
- *petition* as vague catch-all — name the actual ask (*school building*, *leak-proof walls*, *beacon array*); keep *petition* only when the form itself is the point; see Pass 3 §3.2e
- *hold / holds / held* as vague endurance or custody filler (*walls that hold weather*, *if today holds*, *window still held*) — prefer *withstand*, *stay quiet*, *stay open*, *stay on station*, *in custody*; see Pass 3 §3.2f
- unnecessary analogies and synonym rotation for style (*clean pipe for bad news*, *mourning with the volume down*, *honesty as a person*, rotating *silence/absence/emptiness* for the same fact) — use the first plain word; see Pass 3 §3.3k
- *empty* / *went dark* / *returns stopped* (or *expected returns missing*) as default loss shorthand for a colony, channel, or bearing — prefer *missing colony*, *settlement beacons gone*, *attacked* / *taken apart* once known; keep *empty* only for literal containers/rooms/seats; see Pass 3 §3.2g
- *shared warning format* / *warning format* / *shared format* / *joint format* as default packet-path jargon — say where it went and that both sides get the same words (*sent to Contact Node Seven — same words for Fleet and Dominion*); see Pass 3 §3.2h
- *lag* / *lag voice* / *on lag* as default for remote speakers, Helion patches, or pedestals — prefer *on the channel*, *came through*, *from Helion*, *relay*; keep *lag* / *delay* only when time delay itself is the beat; see Pass 3 §3.2i
- *went silent* / *stopped answering* as default for a colony once the attack is known (especially Founders' Reach after live observation) — prefer *attacked* / *taken apart* / *watched it leave*; keep silence vocabulary only for the early unknown; see Pass 3 §3.2j
- *do not invent what you have not seen* / *contradictory orders* / *when orders and sensors disagree* as Helion/watch sermons — prefer the real order (*stay on watch*, *confirm before you name it*); see Pass 3 §3.2k
- *war story* / *war words* as default Helion/gallery catchphrase — prefer *someone to blame*, *invasion talk*, *fighting before we confirm*; see Pass 3 §3.2l

**Prefer:** the concrete failure or ask — *means two actions*, *guess under pressure*, *finished answer*, *category*, *classification*, *fake readiness*, *not a full brief*, name the real term (*distress*, *hold weapons* only when that is the real order).

**Keep *label* only** for literal print (mug label, pedestal labeled for Rowan).

